the results to real systems and interpreting the mathematical results in terms of experimental observations. Ultimately, approximate methods are presented that are used when applying quantum theory in the field of quantum chemistry for the study of real systems like atoms, molecules, and crystals. Both the foundations for the different methods and a broader range of examples of their applications are presented. The textbook assumes no prior knowledge in quantum theory. Moreover, special emphasis is put on interpreting the mathematical results and less on an exact mathematical derivations of those. Finally, each chapter closes with a number of questions and exercises that help in focusing on the main results of the chapter. Many of the exercises include answers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aChemie. 4aChemische Bindung. 4aQuantenmechanik. 4aQuantentheorie. 4aTheoretische Chemie. 7aSCIENCE / Chemistry / Computational & Molecular Modeling.2bisacsh  aChemical bonding.  aComputational chemistry.  aQuantum chemistry.  aTheoretical chemistry.1 aZhou, Meijuan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021 Englishz978311075416208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021z9783110753936oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831107422370 cprintz978311074219040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074220640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110742206423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110742206/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075416-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.S